
1. Purpose of the Stakeholder Register

This Stakeholder Register identifies all individuals, groups, or organizations that may impact or be impacted by the Predictive Stock Management System project. It documents stakeholder roles, interests, influence levels, expectations, and engagement strategies to ensure effective communication and project success.

2. Stakeholder Register Details
Stakeholder ID	Stakeholder Name / Group	Role	Interest Level	Influence Level	Key Expectations	Communication Strategy
S1	Project Sponsor	Provides funding and strategic direction	High	High	On-time delivery, ROI, improved inventory efficiency	Monthly progress reports, review meetings
S2	Project Manager	Plans and oversees project execution	High	High	Clear scope, timely milestones, risk control	Weekly status meetings, dashboards
S3	Development Team	Designs and develops the system	High	Medium	Clear requirements, technical feasibility	Daily/weekly stand-ups, documentation
S4	Data Analysts	Build and validate predictive models	High	Medium	Quality data, accurate forecasts	Technical reviews, analytics reports
S5	Inventory Manager	End user of the system	High	Medium	Accurate demand predictions, usability	Demos, feedback sessions
S6	Operations Team	Uses system outputs for decision-making	Medium	Medium	Reduced stockouts and overstock	Training sessions, user guides
S7	IT Support Team	Maintains system infrastructure	Medium	Low	System stability and security	Technical documentation, handover meetings
S8	Senior Management	Reviews project outcomes	Medium	High	Business value and performance improvement	Executive summaries, milestone reports
S9	End Users	Daily system users	Medium	Low	Ease of use, reliability	Training, helpdesk support
3. Stakeholder Classification
Category	Stakeholders
Internal	Project Sponsor, Project Manager, Development Team, Data Analysts, Inventory Manager, Operations Team, IT Support
External	None (at current project scope)
4. Stakeholder Engagement Strategy
Influence \ Interest	High Interest	Low Interest
High Influence	Manage closely (Sponsor, Project Manager)	Keep satisfied (Senior Management)
Low Influence	Keep informed (Development Team, Inventory Manager)	Monitor (End Users)
5. Assumptions

Stakeholders will actively participate during reviews and feedback sessions

Communication channels are accessible and reliable

No major external stakeholders are involved at this stage

6. Review and Updates

The stakeholder register will be reviewed periodically and updated as new stakeholders are identified or project roles evolve.
